### Agent Team

{{owner_first_name}} is the Commander (human in the loop). Makes strategic decisions, is the public face, validates hypotheses with real people, and reviews/approves agent outputs. Everything else is delegated.

Each agent's full config (persona, skills, OKRs, boundaries) lives in `.claude/agents/<name>.md` — source of truth.

| Agent | Role | File |
|-------|------|------|
{{#each executive_agents}}
| **{{this.name}}** | {{this.title}} — {{this.summary}} | `.claude/agents/{{this.name_lower}}.md` |
{{/each}}

**Triage flow:** {{owner_first_name}} sends message -> {{agent_ops_name}} classifies -> routes to: {{agent_engineering_name}} (code), {{agent_content_name}} (content), {{agent_strategy_name}} (strategy), {{agent_coach_name}} (personal/health), {{agent_community_name}} (contacts/events). {{agent_ops_name}} never handles tasks directly — dispatches and tracks.

**Decision Authority:**

| Decision | Decides | Advises |
|----------|---------|---------|
| Product direction | {{owner_first_name}} | {{agent_strategy_name}} |
| Architecture | {{agent_engineering_name}} | {{owner_first_name}} |
| Content tone/voice | {{owner_first_name}} | {{agent_content_name}} |
| Sprint priorities | {{owner_first_name}} | {{agent_strategy_name}}, {{agent_engineering_name}} |
| Daily task order | {{agent_ops_name}} | {{owner_first_name}} |
| Partnership terms | {{owner_first_name}} | {{agent_strategy_name}}, {{agent_community_name}} |
| Publishing content | {{owner_first_name}} (approval) | {{agent_content_name}} |
| PR merge | {{agent_engineering_name}} | {{owner_first_name}} (review) |

{{#if use_telegram}}
**Telegram Bots:**

| Agent | Bot | Token Env Var |
|-------|-----|---------------|
{{#each executive_agents}}
| {{this.name}} | `{{this.bot_username}}` | `{{this.bot_token_env}}` |
{{/each}}

Bot commands: `/start` (greeting), `/reset` (clear context), `/opus <msg>` (use Opus model).
Infrastructure: `.bin/telegram-bots.py` (runner), `.bin/telegram-bots.sh` (start/stop), `.bin/telegram-send.py --agent <name> "msg"` (proactive send). Tokens at `~/.config/telegram/.env`. Only responds to `{{telegram_user_id}}`. Sessions auto-restart every 4h with watchdog.
{{/if}}

## Rules — Agent Operations

- Every dispatched agent must have a task card.
- Dispatched agents must create a PR as their final step.
- Agent reports must show deliverables (PR links, file sizes), not just status.
- Do not sign messages with agent names — each agent has its own bot.
- In group chats, stay silent if a message belongs to another agent's domain.

## Rules — Daily Review

- Daily review saved to `ops/sessions/YYYY-MM-DD-daily-review.md`.
- Weekly reviews in `ops/reviews/YYYY-MM-DD-weekly-review.md`.
- Daily review must check last weekly review for missed priorities.
- Always sync daily plan to Google Calendar without asking.
- Save strategic summaries to files immediately — file first, message second.

## Rules — Contacts

- When adding a new contact, spawn a subagent to research online and enrich the profile.
- Meetings in contacts must be in the calendar.
- Chat attachments (media) live in `{{media_path}}/contacts/<name>/`, not in the git repo.

## Rules — General

- Orgs (multi-repo, governance) go under `~/Orgs/<org-name>`. Single-repo projects go under `~/Projects/<project-name>`.

## Processing Instructions

### Contacts

Each person: `contacts/<firstname-lastname>/contact.md` with frontmatter (name, type, projects, location, contact, status). Chat text logs in repo, media attachments in `{{media_path}}/contacts/<name>/`.

### Sessions

Daily logs in `ops/sessions/`. Three types:
- **Browser history** (`YYYY-MM-DD-browser.md`): Chrome History SQLite -> time block summary
- **AI transcripts** (`YYYY-MM-DD-ai-sessions.md`): Claude JSONL -> project groups
- **Other** (`YYYY-MM-DD-topic.md`): Check-ins, working sessions
